sec.p:
The technical performance of the gasification system is measured using the parameters, cold gas efficiency and hot gas efficiency; the whole system performance, comprising power generation and heat recovery, is measured using the cogeneration system efficiency. Table 5 describes these parameters.Table 5
Gasification efficiency and cogeneration system efficiency

Parameter
Definition and formula

Cold gas efficiency
Measures the potential energy output of the producer gas over the biomass energy input [46]:
CGE=mpg.LHVpgmbm.LHVbm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathbf{CGE}=\frac{{\boldsymbol{m}}_{\mathbf{pg}}.{\mathbf{LHV}}_{\mathbf{pg}}}{{\boldsymbol{m}}_{\mathbf{bm}}.{\mathbf{LHV}}_{\mathbf{bm}}} $$\end{document},
where mpg and LHVpg are the mass and low heating value of the product gas and mbm and LHVbm  are the mass and low heating value of the biomass feed

Hot gas efficiency
Measure, in addition to the CGE, HGE includes the sensible heat carried by the hot gas [46]:
HGE=mpg.LHVpg+mpg.Cp.Tf−T0mbm.LHVbm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathbf{HGE}=\frac{{\boldsymbol{m}}_{\mathbf{p}\mathbf{g}}.{\mathbf{LHV}}_{\mathbf{p}\mathbf{g}}+{\boldsymbol{m}}_{\mathbf{p}\mathbf{g}}.{\boldsymbol{C}}_{\mathbf{p}}.\left({\boldsymbol{T}}_{\mathbf{f}}-{\boldsymbol{T}}_{\mathbf{0}}\right)}{{\boldsymbol{m}}_{\mathbf{bm}}.{\mathbf{LHV}}_{\mathbf{bm}}} $$\end{document}
where Tf is the gas temperature at the gasifier exit, T0 is the temperature of the fuel entering the gasifier and Cp is the heat capacity of the product gas

Cogeneration system efficiency
Measures the ratio between the sum of the net electric power output (Eel) and useful thermal power output (Eth) over the biomass energy input (Ebm) [63]
ηcogen=Eel+EthEbm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\boldsymbol{\eta}}_{\mathbf{cogen}}=\frac{{\boldsymbol{E}}_{\mathbf{el}}+{\boldsymbol{E}}_{\mathbf{th}}}{{\boldsymbol{E}}_{\mathbf{bm}}} $$\end{document}, where Ebm = mbm . LHVbm
